<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Sathe</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-16 22:52:17</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>First of all when you look at an item, you also have to look at its rarity. Just to get in to sebilis you need a key or a rogue. It is also a very high lv dungeon, lowest lv there is 44 I believe. That combined with it is currently the best ring for wis based casters in the game, makes it worth 10kpp. This is not an item for someone to buy if all they have is 10kpp its for maxing out your mana. For example if I have the best of everything for every slot, except rings then this item is well worth the 10kpp for me. If I have 10kpp to spend on items for a twinked druid, I would buy things like RMB's, foremans tunic, etc. So, yes, this item is worth 10k just not to most of the lower lv players.<BR>
<BR>
49th Druid of Quellious</font></td></tr></table>
