<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Wulefgarr</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-19 20:17:30</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I agree that rarity has some bearing on the value of an item, however, the overall benefit of an item has to be examined. If you already have the Plat Jasper rings that are AC 0 , +6 Wis, the overall benefit of this item would be +2 AC, +2 Str, and +10 mana. If this is work 10k pp to you, then yes, it is worth 10k pp. But for me, despite my bankroll, it is not worth that kind of cash. Would I wear it if I won it in a roll? Yes. Would I pay 10k pp? No.<BR>
<BR>
Just my 2cp on the subject.<BR>
<BR>
Happy hunting.</font></td></tr></table>
